<p>Dave talks about a tech support issue he had with his Mac setup this weekend, and how it&#8217;s bad to assume anything without confirming it first! John and Dave then answer your questions about Automounting volumes at startup, copying your iTunes library, cloning drives, and more!</p>
<p><strong>Show notes for TMO To Go: Mac Geek Gab For May 15th, 2006</strong></p>
<p>Direct Links: <a href="http://mp3.macobserver.com/podcast/mgg53.mp3" data-wpel-link="external" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">MP3 Version</a> or <a href="http://mp3.macobserver.com/podcast/mgg53e.m4b" data-wpel-link="external" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">AAC Enhanced Version</a> (courtesy of <a href="http://forums.krazynonsense.com/" data-wpel-link="external" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Michael, aka Computernap!</a>).</p>
<p>Dave talks about a tech support issue he had with his Mac setup this weekend, and how it&#8217;s bad to assume anything without confirming it first! John and Dave then answer your questions about Automounting volumes at startup, copying your iTunes library, cloning drives, and more!</p>
